daily_routine: Every morning at 5:30 AM, Carmen would check water temperature readings
  from the reef monitoring buoys, then prepare dive equipment for tourists wanting
  to see the coral restoration sites. She'd spend hours underwater tending to coral
  fragments in PVC nursery trees, photographing growth progress, and guiding visitors
  through the underwater sculpture garden built on dead reef substrate. Evenings were
  for community meetings about reef restoration funding and coordinating with other
  Caribbean coral restoration projects
