last_days_scenario: The summer of 2041 brought water temperatures that stayed above
  86Â°F for three consecutive months. Carmen watched her coral nurseries bleach white
  in a matter of days, then dissolve into chalky fragments. The dive boats stopped
  coming when there was nothing left to see but gray rubble. Her neighbors - boat
  captains, restaurant owners, souvenir shop keepers - left one by one as tourist
  dollars evaporated. Carmen remained alone in her concrete house, checking empty
  monitoring buoys each morning, radioing daily reports to a research station that
  had stopped responding. She kept feeding the last surviving coral fragments in her
  makeshift home aquarium system, even as the power grid failed and the desalination
  plant shut down
